[[File:BTR2 monaural recorder (1954-1970), Abbey Road Studios.jpg|thumb|right|A British Tape Recorder (BTR) used to record music at the [[Abbey Road Studios]]]]
The '''EMI Archive Trust''' is the charity which was established in 1996 to hold and maintain the archives of the [[EMI]] company and its parent companies such as the [[Gramophone Company]].<ref name=EAT/>  The archives are located in [[Hayes, Hillingdon|Hayes]], where the company had its main factories, and contain many antique recordings.<ref name=G/>

